# Import Standards

## Path Resolution
- **ALWAYS** use tsconfig paths (`@/`) instead of relative imports
- Import from `@/utils/config` instead of `../utils/config`
- Import from `@/commands` instead of `../commands`

## Module Organization
- **NO** barrel exports (`index.ts` files) - import directly from specific files
- Be explicit about imports - avoid re-exports
- Each file should have a single responsibility

## Examples

✅ **Good:**
```typescript
import { ConfigManager } from '@/utils/config/config-manager';
import { Logger } from '@/utils/logging/logger';
```

❌ **Bad:**
```typescript
import { ConfigManager } from '../../../utils/config/config-manager';
import { Logger } from '@/utils'; // barrel export
```
